  inkblot: A simple hack to play around with adding, positioning 
           images to screen. Uses inkyPHAT cal example as starting
           point. 

  Source <https://learn.pimoroni.com/tutorial/sandyj/getting-started-with-inky-phat>


2020JUL12
* able to load an image to screen

* fonts
- if you want to use a font, try the following:

    know where to find your fonts. On a RPi system, 

        <https://wiki.debian.org/Fonts#Adding_fonts>

    locally on your system use:
    
        fc-list 

    know how to load a font

        <https://pillow.readthedocs.io/en/stable/reference/ImageFont.html> 

* images
- want to draw an image to screen?

      <https://pillow.readthedocs.io/en/stable/reference/Image.html> 

Resources

[1] Title created with an ASCII text generator using 'slant' and 'stretch=Yes". 
The code is based on Figlet which can be found here ~ <http://www.figlet.org/>
